"playing songs I’m familiar with."

592
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:52,640
"the galleries…"

593
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:55,040
"Everything fills my mind"

594
00:55:55,440 --> 00:55:56,400
"and my imagination."

595
00:55:56,800 --> 00:56:00,320
"And my heart is in a place where I finally belong."

596
00:56:01,040 --> 00:56:03,120
"It’s a place where ideas bloom endlessly."

597
00:56:14,240 --> 00:56:15,160
"As for Phe…"

598
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:17,040
"after coming back to New York,"

599
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:19,160
"he quit gambling for good,"

600
00:56:19,440 --> 00:56:22,480
"paid to have the front door rebuilt,
stronger than before,"

601
00:56:23,040 --> 00:56:25,880
"and started taking his work
at his restaurant, seriously."

602
00:56:26,800 --> 00:56:27,800
What are you doing, Phe?

603
00:56:32,960 --> 00:56:34,480
Did you have to ruin the whole set?

604
00:56:37,200 --> 00:56:39,720
Well, I had to defend myself at that moment.

605
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:47,520
Other than paying off the debts,

606
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,960
I’ve got to start over collecting all this stuff too.

607
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:56,160
You didn’t have to buy everything new.

608
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:57,880
You could’ve fixed them.

609
00:56:58,360 --> 00:56:59,000
Look.

610
00:56:59,520 --> 00:57:00,960
Glue it back together and it’s fine.

611
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:03,840
Maybe.

612
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:06,040
Some things

613
00:57:06,840 --> 00:57:07,920
can be fixed, maybe.

614
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:29,600
Uno.

615
00:57:30,080 --> 00:57:30,680
Game.

616
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:32,480
"At first, it was lonely."

617
00:57:32,800 --> 00:57:35,400
"But I was lucky to have Jeong-Ah and Angie,"

618
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:37,480
"who helped me with so many things,"

619
00:57:38,280 --> 00:57:40,840
"and became the people
I spent most of my time with."

620
00:57:41,520 --> 00:57:44,160
"To be honest, they made me miss
Jieab and the others too."

621
00:57:47,960 --> 00:57:48,400
So…

622
00:57:48,520 --> 00:57:49,760
How was your work?

623
00:57:50,000 --> 00:57:51,400
It’s pretty good, actually.

624
00:57:51,680 --> 00:57:53,480
And I really enjoyed it here.

625
00:57:55,200 --> 00:57:55,760
Oh!

626
00:57:57,320 --> 00:57:58,320
Just a moment, okay?

627
00:57:59,560 --> 00:58:02,880
"Catherine, she’s a lecturer at the university."

628
00:58:03,720 --> 00:58:07,240
"She’s been helping me
ever since I first started my master’s."

629
00:58:08,120 --> 00:58:09,240
"After that,"

630
00:58:09,560 --> 00:58:12,400
